
Overview of adj scratchy

The adj scratchy has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (1) abrasive, scratchy -- (causing abrasion)
2. cranky, fractious, irritable, nettlesome, peevish, peckish, pettish, petulant, scratchy, testy, tetchy, techy -- (easily irritated or annoyed; "an incorrigibly fractious young man"; "not the least nettlesome of his countrymen")
3. spotty, uneven, scratchy -- (lacking consistency; "the golfer hit the ball well but his putting was spotty")
4. grating, gravelly, rasping, raspy, rough, scratchy -- (unpleasantly harsh or grating in sound; "a gravelly voice")
